The Tronto (Latin: Truentus) is a 115 km-long Italian river that arises at Monte della Laghetta and ends in the Adriatic Sea at Porto d'Ascoli, San Benedetto del Tronto. Anciently the Truentus, it traverses the Lazio, Marche, and Abruzzo regions. Coordinates: 4254N 1355E / 42.9N 13.917E / 42.9; 13.917
